♪Look at the heavy rain pouring down♪

44
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:58,217
♪Can't compare to you and me
sitting in silence♪

45
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:01,727
(Yan Tuo: Get rest early.)

46
00:05:09,991 --> 00:05:15,614
♪Your smile, the desire for your palm♪

47
00:05:15,792 --> 00:05:20,198
♪Holding the starlight,
tight and not letting go♪

48
00:05:20,464 --> 00:05:21,360
(Luo)

49
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:24,544
♪Look at the flowing clouds like fire♪

50
00:05:24,544 --> 00:05:27,047
♪Look at the dancing moon shadows♪

51
00:05:27,294 --> 00:05:32,656
♪Still can't compare to you and me,
every moment♪

52
00:05:52,496 --> 00:05:57,328
(Fortune)

53
00:06:21,088 --> 00:06:21,888
Mr. Yan.

54
00:06:26,287 --> 00:06:27,128
Fixed it?

55
00:06:45,448 --> 00:06:46,008
Yes.

56
00:07:45,847 --> 00:07:46,727
It's been so long.

57
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:49,287
Lin Xirou should've already known

58
00:07:49,287 --> 00:07:50,688
Yan Tuo was rescued.

59
00:07:51,927 --> 00:07:53,568
But there is no news so far.

60
00:07:54,287 --> 00:07:55,648
That makes me feel uneasy.

61
00:07:58,167 --> 00:07:59,128
I'll be careful.

62
00:08:03,807 --> 00:08:06,568
Should I bring Lin Ling and Liu Changxi

63
00:08:06,847 --> 00:08:08,328
to the South Mountain base first?

64
00:08:09,287 --> 00:08:11,208
That can ease your pressure.

65
00:08:14,807 --> 00:08:15,968
That place doesn't suit them.

66
00:08:17,008 --> 00:08:18,727
I can handle it for now.

67
00:08:20,807 --> 00:08:22,367
Lin Xirou has no more cards to play.

68
00:08:23,487 --> 00:08:25,047
I have no idea what she might do.

69
00:08:28,128 --> 00:08:28,807
Got it.

70
00:08:32,088 --> 00:08:34,328
Update me anytime.

71
00:08:57,607 --> 00:08:59,367
We might take action recently.

72
00:09:01,328 --> 00:09:02,527
I suggested to Xing Shen

73
00:09:03,048 --> 00:09:04,288
that you could join us.

74
00:09:06,288 --> 00:09:07,448
Are you pitying me?

75
00:09:09,288 --> 00:09:10,208
I'm inviting you.

76
00:09:12,208 --> 00:09:13,367
But I still feel

77
00:09:14,088 --> 00:09:15,487
I can't fully integrate with you.

78
00:09:20,808 --> 00:09:23,168
When badgers dig burrows,

79
00:09:23,727 --> 00:09:25,968
they drive animals out from underground,

80
00:09:26,168 --> 00:09:27,487
so coyotes can catch them.

81
00:09:28,247 --> 00:09:30,727
When coyotes chase prey,

82
00:09:30,928 --> 00:09:32,688
they also drive them into burrows,

83
00:09:32,887 --> 00:09:34,127
so badgers can catch them.

84
00:09:34,367 --> 00:09:35,767
They're different species,

85
00:09:36,168 --> 00:09:37,088
but working together

86
00:09:37,408 --> 00:09:38,647
is still a better choice.

87
00:09:49,088 --> 00:09:50,208
Ever since meeting Jiang,

88
00:09:51,367 --> 00:09:53,408
my life has revolved around him.

89
00:09:55,168 --> 00:09:56,007
I used to think

90
00:09:56,968 --> 00:09:57,767
that without him,

91
00:09:57,887 --> 00:09:59,127
my life would collapse.

92
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:01,928
But now,

93
00:10:03,367 --> 00:10:05,607
even if I'm a badger hiding underground,

94
00:10:06,647 --> 00:10:08,328
I can still meet coyote friends.

95
00:10:15,887 --> 00:10:16,647
Continue.

96
00:11:13,487 --> 00:11:15,367
Ms. Lu, where are the eggs?

97
00:11:15,647 --> 00:11:16,288
Over here.

98
00:11:24,847 --> 00:11:25,527
Eggs.

99
00:11:25,847 --> 00:11:26,487
Thanks.

100
00:11:30,127 --> 00:11:31,168
No more dumplings.

101
00:11:31,168 --> 00:11:32,767
The fridge can't hold anymore.

102
00:11:32,808 --> 00:11:33,568
This is different.

103
00:11:33,568 --> 00:11:35,448
I'm making wontons this time.

104
00:11:35,448 --> 00:11:36,808
Don't those also go in the fridge?

105
00:11:38,247 --> 00:11:39,007
Tuo.

106
00:11:39,168 --> 00:11:40,007
Is this enough?

107
00:11:40,007 --> 00:11:41,288
Yes. Chop them, please.

108
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:42,007
Okay.

109
00:11:42,887 --> 00:11:44,007
What should I cut them into?

110
00:11:44,127 --> 00:11:45,847
Into small ones. Watch your fingers.

111
00:11:45,928 --> 00:11:46,487
Got it.

112
00:11:52,168 --> 00:11:53,448
You better think it through.

113
00:11:55,408 --> 00:11:56,448
What?

114
00:11:57,688 --> 00:11:58,767
Now,

115
00:11:58,767 --> 00:12:00,808
their whole family is here.

116
00:12:03,168 --> 00:12:05,288
You always complained
that the house was too quiet.

117
00:12:05,568 --> 00:12:07,208
Now, you're finding it annoying?

118
00:12:07,928 --> 00:12:09,607
Your pleasure matters most.

119
00:12:16,408 --> 00:12:17,007
Morning.

120
00:12:20,288 --> 00:12:20,928
Morning.

121
00:12:27,487 --> 00:12:29,968
Mr. Yan is such a good cook.

122
00:12:30,887 --> 00:12:31,767
I can say

123
00:12:31,847 --> 00:12:33,847
Tuo is an instant noodle expert.

124
00:12:34,992 --> 00:12:36,688
Grew up pretty much on our own.

125
00:12:36,688 --> 00:12:37,887
So I made instant noodles

126
00:12:37,887 --> 00:12:39,087
for Lin Ling in various ways.

127
00:12:39,087 --> 00:12:40,247
Soaked, boiled, or dry mixed.

128
00:12:50,328 --> 00:12:51,127
Come on, Ling.

129
00:12:51,208 --> 00:12:52,048
Try wontons.

130
00:12:56,727 --> 00:12:58,328
The other day, Mr. Lu asked me

131
00:12:58,416 --> 00:12:59,664
if I wanted to participate

132
00:12:59,664 --> 00:13:00,624
in a showcase exhibition

133
00:13:00,624 --> 00:13:01,607
of Lawrence Art Gallery.

134
00:13:02,328 --> 00:13:04,487
What's a showcase exhibition?

135
00:13:05,208 --> 00:13:06,208
Ever had a fruit platter?

136
00:13:07,568 --> 00:13:08,607
A braised meat platter.

137
00:13:09,328 --> 00:13:11,527
It's like putting
similar things together.

138
00:13:11,527 --> 00:13:12,088
Mr. Changxi.

139
00:13:12,487 --> 00:13:13,288
It should be...

140
00:13:13,288 --> 00:13:14,288
a joint exhibition.

141
00:13:14,808 --> 00:13:16,247
That means gathering

142
00:13:16,247 --> 00:13:17,408
several talented sculptors

143
00:13:17,408 --> 00:13:18,048
in one place

144
00:13:18,048 --> 00:13:19,088
for a major exhibition.

145
00:13:19,168 --> 00:13:20,048
Exactly.

146
00:13:21,007 --> 00:13:22,048
If I were exceptional,

147
00:13:22,048 --> 00:13:23,088
I'd get a solo exhibition.

148
00:13:23,247 --> 00:13:24,928
It also means I need to work harder.

149
00:13:25,328 --> 00:13:26,007
Not at all.

150
00:13:26,127 --> 00:13:27,127
It's fine.

151
00:13:27,527 --> 00:13:30,367
You need energy to work harder, right?

152
00:13:31,088 --> 00:13:32,088
Eat up.

153
00:13:32,288 --> 00:13:33,127
Let's eat.

154
00:13:34,192 --> 00:13:37,424
(Joy Comes Upon)

155
00:13:49,168 --> 00:13:50,480
(Mr. Lu)

156
00:13:54,568 --> 00:13:55,127
Hello.

157
00:13:55,688 --> 00:13:57,487
Have you prepared
all the required documents?

158
00:13:59,647 --> 00:14:01,127
I was just about to tell you.

159
00:14:01,448 --> 00:14:02,607
Some of my pieces

160
00:14:02,607 --> 00:14:03,647
don't suit the exhibition.

161
00:14:04,247 --> 00:14:05,208
Stop it.

162
00:14:05,448 --> 00:14:06,408
It's a rare chance.

163
00:14:06,887 --> 00:14:08,168
It's just a joint exhibition,

164
00:14:08,328 --> 00:14:10,367
but every participating artist

165
00:14:10,408 --> 00:14:12,487
is a rising star gaining momentum.

166
00:14:13,247 --> 00:14:14,487
If you can't decide,

167
00:14:14,568 --> 00:14:16,168
I'll just send over a Hermit Duck piece.

168
00:14:20,808 --> 00:14:21,887
Give me some time.

169
00:14:21,887 --> 00:14:23,568
Staying low-key

170
00:14:23,968 --> 00:14:25,127
and following your whims

171
00:14:25,487 --> 00:14:26,127
will leave us

172
00:14:26,127 --> 00:14:28,007
struggling to make ends meet.

173
00:14:28,607 --> 00:14:30,088
After all, our talent has its limits.

174
00:14:30,568 --> 00:14:31,847
We need to face reality.

175
00:14:32,568 --> 00:14:33,767
Listen to me,

176
00:14:33,767 --> 00:14:34,647
you should...

177
00:14:55,928 --> 00:14:58,247
You've just recovered,

178
00:14:58,568 --> 00:15:00,048
so focus on internal wellness.

179
00:15:00,568 --> 00:15:02,527
Once your blood circulates smoothly,

180
00:15:02,727 --> 00:15:07,168
your internal organs like heart,
liver, spleen, lungs, and kidneys

181
00:15:07,408 --> 00:15:10,487
can function properly.

182
00:15:11,288 --> 00:15:15,568
Next, drawing the bow.

183
00:15:18,068 --> 00:15:18,568
Mr. Changxi.

184
00:15:18,568 --> 00:15:20,088
I can't deal with this patience thing.

185
00:15:20,168 --> 00:15:22,048
These exercises are good
for you and Ms. Lu.

186
00:15:22,847 --> 00:15:24,887
Ling, how about I take you
for strength training?

187
00:15:25,328 --> 00:15:25,968
Me?

188
00:15:27,048 --> 00:15:28,048
All this stiff muscle

189
00:15:28,048 --> 00:15:29,808
is just for show.

190
00:15:30,288 --> 00:15:32,448
Nourishing yourself from the inside out

191
00:15:32,487 --> 00:15:34,928
is what truly benefits you.

192
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:37,408
These are treasures
passed down by our ancestors.

193
00:15:37,408 --> 00:15:38,328
You understand nothing.

194
00:15:38,887 --> 00:15:39,928
Ling, don't listen to him.

195
00:15:39,928 --> 00:15:40,767
Follow my pace.

196
00:15:41,767 --> 00:15:42,408
Straighten up.

197
00:15:57,168 --> 00:15:58,007
What's the matter?

198
00:16:00,928 --> 00:16:01,928
Do you think

199
00:16:02,247 --> 00:16:03,928
I have any real talent

200
00:16:05,048 --> 00:16:06,127
on sculpting?

201
00:16:07,208 --> 00:16:08,328
What's wrong?

202
00:16:09,288 --> 00:16:10,088
Just asking.

203
00:16:12,288 --> 00:16:13,328
Is it because

204
00:16:13,527 --> 00:16:15,168
the showcase exhibition?

205
00:16:20,887 --> 00:16:22,887
If you don't want to go, then don't.

206
00:16:23,127 --> 00:16:24,408
You can't excel at everything.

207
00:16:24,847 --> 00:16:25,647
What do you mean?

208
00:16:26,288 --> 00:16:27,007
Look,

209
00:16:28,527 --> 00:16:31,127
you're beautiful and highly skilled,

210
00:16:31,408 --> 00:16:33,048
both smart and compassionate.

211
00:16:33,328 --> 00:16:34,928
Most importantly, you are discerning

212
00:16:35,007 --> 00:16:36,007
in judging people.

213
00:16:37,408 --> 00:16:38,048
Come on.

214
00:16:38,048 --> 00:16:39,288
Don't try to flatter me.

215
00:16:39,887 --> 00:16:41,127
I know my limits.

216
00:16:45,328 --> 00:16:46,767
Hard work pays off.

217
00:16:48,408 --> 00:16:49,288
Just work hard,

218
00:16:49,288 --> 00:16:50,448
and you'll obtain something.

219
00:16:50,887 --> 00:16:51,607
Look at me.

220
00:16:52,328 --> 00:16:53,727
I've been exercising daily lately.

221
00:16:53,727 --> 00:16:55,208
I'm almost fully recovered now.

222
00:16:56,007 --> 00:16:56,847
I even feel

223
00:16:56,847 --> 00:16:58,727
bodyweight workouts
aren't cutting it anymore.

224
00:16:58,767 --> 00:17:00,088
Any gyms around here?

225
00:17:00,208 --> 00:17:01,408
Take it easy.

226
00:17:01,568 --> 00:17:03,048
You just got recovered.

227
00:17:03,168 --> 00:17:04,287
Don't overestimate yourself.

228
00:17:05,928 --> 00:17:07,567
And back when we were kids,

229
00:17:07,688 --> 00:17:09,208
there were no gyms at all.

230
00:17:09,928 --> 00:17:11,247
We just used whatever was around.

231
00:17:12,047 --> 00:17:15,448
Like buckets, logs,

232
00:17:15,487 --> 00:17:17,608
stones, tires...

233
00:17:18,888 --> 00:17:19,648
Even

234
00:17:20,767 --> 00:17:21,487
training partners.

235
00:17:22,648 --> 00:17:23,368
Training partners?

236
00:17:34,567 --> 00:17:35,727
Three.

237
00:17:48,928 --> 00:17:50,567
When you do more than ten,

238
00:17:50,567 --> 00:17:51,888
I'll get you a gym membership.

239
00:17:51,928 --> 00:17:52,527
Wait.

240
00:17:52,807 --> 00:17:54,727
I can't keep my balance like this.

241
00:17:55,047 --> 00:17:56,527
Why copy the Ninja Duck?

242
00:17:56,767 --> 00:17:57,608
That doesn't count.

243
00:18:00,928 --> 00:18:01,567
Fine.

244
00:18:01,968 --> 00:18:02,688
It doesn't count.

245
00:18:06,128 --> 00:18:07,368
Can you keep your balance now?

246
00:18:12,487 --> 00:18:13,287
Four.

247
00:18:25,487 --> 00:18:26,087
Wait.

248
00:18:26,968 --> 00:18:29,327
You said you can't keep your balance.

249
00:18:29,327 --> 00:18:29,928
Wait.

250
00:18:30,047 --> 00:18:31,287
This one doesn't count either.

251
00:18:31,287 --> 00:18:32,368
I'm out of energy.

252
00:18:33,208 --> 00:18:35,168
So what would make it count?

253
00:18:48,327 --> 00:18:49,007
I...

254
00:18:51,247 --> 00:18:51,968
I want...

255
00:19:21,936 --> 00:19:23,408
(1 Message)

256
00:19:44,807 --> 00:19:45,928
The Earth Fiend replied.

257
00:19:58,168 --> 00:19:59,567
I tried to live

258
00:19:59,567 --> 00:20:02,567
among humans under rules and law,

259
00:20:02,928 --> 00:20:06,408
without offending
the South Mountain Hunters.

260
00:20:07,287 --> 00:20:10,848
But it was just my wild imagination
and wishful thinking.

261
00:20:11,527 --> 00:20:12,928
Even unwilling to do it,

262
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:15,608
I must still do it.

263
00:20:17,287 --> 00:20:19,168
You can claim it a declaration of war,

264
00:20:19,608 --> 00:20:21,448
or just an invitation.

265
00:20:22,527 --> 00:20:23,807
Ten days from now,

266
00:20:23,888 --> 00:20:26,888
bring everyone you and I captured.

267
00:20:27,688 --> 00:20:29,848
Let's settle everything face-to-face.

268
00:20:30,368 --> 00:20:32,287
I've picked the location.

269
00:20:33,727 --> 00:20:36,448
The place where we first met,

270
00:20:37,727 --> 00:20:39,168
Twilight Chasm

271
00:20:39,767 --> 00:20:41,007
under the Golden Gate.

272
00:20:47,608 --> 00:20:49,688
Letting go of what I have

273
00:20:49,888 --> 00:20:51,688
does pain me deeply.

274
00:20:52,767 --> 00:20:54,527
But then again,

275
00:20:55,408 --> 00:20:56,807
what I've gained

276
00:20:57,767 --> 00:20:59,287
is more than enough.

277
00:21:00,287 --> 00:21:01,208
Besides,

278
00:21:02,168 --> 00:21:03,608
I have time.

279
00:21:04,567 --> 00:21:06,368
I have plenty of time.

280
00:21:07,688 --> 00:21:08,888
I can afford to wait

281
00:21:09,567 --> 00:21:11,007
and to waste.

282
00:21:13,007 --> 00:21:15,608
I remember every one of you,

283
00:21:16,087 --> 00:21:20,247
your families and descendants.

